pageContext.description: Edge worn, corners bent, broken and worn.  Deep circular hole (recently) bored in R. side. Decorated with bands of small incised lines.  Sides probably hammered into lozenges, but much worn.
pageContext.patina: Olive green patina on face. Deep bright green on reverse.
pageContext.surface: A good deal scraped and scratched and pitted.
pageContext.other: Site: unspecified location in Yorkshire - geolocation not accurate to 10 kms,Width: edge 114mm; butt 30mm,Weight: 912.95 gms
pageContext.composition: Mr. Gowland's analysis: Copper 85.83; Tin 11.73; Lead 1.21; Iron 0.10; Nickle 0.14; Silver a trace
pageContext.publications: Evans, fig. 4,Horae Ferales Pl. IV, fig. 4
